WEBVTT

00:01.922 --> 00:03.294
♪ Thugger, thugger ♪

00:03.294 --> 00:05.046
Dre:
 I love feeling special...

00:05.046 --> 00:07.178
♪ Appreciate the love
at all times ♪

00:07.178 --> 00:08.889
...getting
 the first-class treatment.

00:08.889 --> 00:10.721
♪ Dig, I feel special ♪

00:10.721 --> 00:13.934
It's as American
 as apple pie and baseball --

00:13.934 --> 00:16.767
Well, back-in-the-day baseball
 before steroids,

00:16.767 --> 00:19.690
but not so far back
 that it was segregated.

00:19.690 --> 00:21.942
You know what? Let's just
 stick with apple pie --

00:21.942 --> 00:23.604
Delicious.

00:23.604 --> 00:25.406
But, look, it's not just me.

00:25.406 --> 00:27.698
Everybody loves
 special treatment.

00:27.698 --> 00:30.491
It's that thing that says
 you're different,

00:30.491 --> 00:33.364
you're the best,
 you deserve shrimp.

00:33.364 --> 00:36.957
So that's why when it came time
 to plan a family vacation,

00:36.957 --> 00:39.039
I knew I wanted to ball out.

00:39.039 --> 00:40.331
Disney World, huh?
Nice.

00:40.331 --> 00:41.292
Dre: Mm-hmm.

00:41.292 --> 00:43.544
Oh, no.
Not just Disney World.

00:43.544 --> 00:45.966
Disney World V.I.P.

00:45.966 --> 00:46.927
-Ooh.
-Mm.

00:46.927 --> 00:47.968
I'm gonna give my kids

00:47.968 --> 00:50.221
the first-class experience
I never had.

00:50.221 --> 00:53.344
Boy, I sure would like to
take Eustace to Disney World,

00:53.344 --> 00:55.846
but I'm not allowed to
take him out of state.

00:55.846 --> 00:58.389
Nor anywhere in my car.

00:58.389 --> 01:00.020
It's just how it is.

01:00.020 --> 01:02.233
When are you leaving?

01:02.233 --> 01:04.185
Tomorrow morning.
And it's gonna be insane.

01:04.185 --> 01:06.237
All right, everyone.
Call your wives.

01:06.237 --> 01:07.778
Tell them
you won't be coming home

01:07.778 --> 01:10.451
'cause you're working late,
only this time, it'll be true.

01:10.451 --> 01:11.532
What's going on?

01:11.532 --> 01:12.783
It's a real crisis.

01:12.783 --> 01:15.406
All hands on deck
for the next two weeks.

01:15.406 --> 01:17.368
Just got an e-mail
from Microsoft.

01:17.368 --> 01:19.250
They hate the direction
we're headed in.

01:19.250 --> 01:21.041
What?
No, can't that wait?

01:21.041 --> 01:22.333
[ Chuckles ]

01:22.333 --> 01:24.835
Subject line --
"We cannot wait."

01:24.835 --> 01:26.797
Look, I can't do it.

01:26.797 --> 01:28.209
I'm going on vacation
tomorrow, man.

01:28.209 --> 01:30.381
I need this.
I've been working hard.

01:30.381 --> 01:31.712
Are you kidding me?

01:31.712 --> 01:33.304
None of you have
done [bleep] around here

01:33.304 --> 01:35.015
since Pokémon Go
came out.

01:37.888 --> 01:42.483
Ohh!

01:42.483 --> 01:44.024
Don't act innocent.
No.

01:44.024 --> 01:45.186
It's exercise.

01:45.186 --> 01:46.227
I can't do it.

01:46.227 --> 01:48.899
Excuse me.
You are running point on this.

01:48.899 --> 01:51.612
Yes, I am, and --

01:51.612 --> 01:52.653
Charlie can do it.

01:52.653 --> 01:53.824
Whe-- hm.

01:53.824 --> 01:55.496
Mm-hmm.

01:55.496 --> 01:58.409
Yeah. Yeah, that's right,
I -- I can do that. Yeah.

01:58.409 --> 02:00.040
You'll be great,
Charlie.

02:00.040 --> 02:02.703
Look, and if you have any
questions, just call me.

02:02.703 --> 02:03.704
[ Chuckles ]

02:03.704 --> 02:05.085
Are you sure you
can handle this?

02:05.085 --> 02:07.628
It is around-the-clock
responsibility.

02:07.628 --> 02:09.419
I've been living here
for two months anyway.

02:09.419 --> 02:11.131
They're tenting my apartment
for ghosts.

02:11.131 --> 02:12.553
Weird things
are happening.

02:12.553 --> 02:15.306
All my shoelaces are missing
and all my forks are flat.

02:15.306 --> 02:16.597
So I haven't been back
since.

02:16.597 --> 02:17.558
[ Chuckles ]

02:17.558 --> 02:19.019
Eustace!

02:19.850 --> 02:23.103
What?
God sakes.

02:23.103 --> 02:27.528
So just like that, the Johnsons
were off on our special trip.

02:27.528 --> 02:28.979
I'm going to Disney World.

02:31.732 --> 02:33.984
♪♪

02:33.984 --> 02:36.367
♪ Nothing can stop me,
I'm all the way up ♪

02:36.367 --> 02:38.199
♪ Oh, all the way up ♪
 Mnh. Got it.

02:38.199 --> 02:40.331
It started with a luxurious
 ride to the airport.

02:40.331 --> 02:41.912
[ Engine starts ]

02:41.912 --> 02:44.705
Then we all enjoyed
 a first-class flight.

02:44.705 --> 02:46.997
Me especially.

02:46.997 --> 02:48.959
And then we arrived
 at Disney World

02:48.959 --> 02:53.173
ready to get turnt on our
 very special V.I.P. vacation

02:53.173 --> 02:56.136
at the most magical place
 on earth.

02:56.136 --> 02:57.388
♪ I'm all the way up ♪

02:57.388 --> 03:00.511
Guys, we are here,
and it's a dream!

03:00.511 --> 03:02.763
Crowds and 100% humidity.
Ain't like no dream I ever had.

03:02.763 --> 03:03.804
Oh, my God!

03:03.804 --> 03:05.686
You know what?
You didn't have to come.

03:05.686 --> 03:07.688
Yes, I did.
I rented your place on Airbnb,

03:07.688 --> 03:09.400
and I'm making
a killing, too.

03:09.400 --> 03:11.692
Hey, guys. Guys, what ride
are we gonna ride first?

03:11.692 --> 03:13.314
I think the faster,
the better.

03:13.314 --> 03:15.075
I want something
that's gonna give me

03:15.075 --> 03:16.867
that same rush I feel
when I drink after

03:16.867 --> 03:18.319
a random co-worker.

03:18.319 --> 03:20.160
I can't wait to do
Space Mountain.

03:20.160 --> 03:22.703
Uh, actually, friend,
you're gonna have to wait.

03:22.703 --> 03:24.495
What do you mean?

03:24.495 --> 03:25.826
Space Mountain has
a height requirement.

03:25.826 --> 03:27.788
Here's a map
I pre-marked.

03:27.788 --> 03:31.131
It's for someone with
your humiliating shortness.

03:31.131 --> 03:34.214
Small World? Dumbo?

03:34.214 --> 03:36.467
I don't want to do
baby rides.

03:36.467 --> 03:38.929
Then get ready to enjoy
43 square miles

03:38.929 --> 03:40.761
of restaurants
and bathrooms.

03:40.761 --> 03:42.343
[ Chuckles ]

03:42.343 --> 03:45.055
[ Laughter ]

03:45.055 --> 03:46.437
We're going there!

03:46.437 --> 03:47.608
Let's go do it!

03:47.608 --> 03:49.350
Hello, Johnson family!

03:49.350 --> 03:50.271
-Oh, hey.
-Oh, hey.

03:50.271 --> 03:52.232
I'm Cody,
and you better be ready

03:52.232 --> 03:54.485
to have a magical day!

03:54.485 --> 03:56.447
-Better be?
-Earl, Earl, get my Vaseline.

03:56.447 --> 03:58.529
-Who is this?
-Mama, mama, mama, mama.

03:58.529 --> 04:00.991
Talking about "better be"?
 Mama. This is Cody.

04:00.991 --> 04:04.325
He's our V.I.P. tour guide,
all right? We bought him.

04:04.325 --> 04:06.537
Oh, well, you didn't actually
buy me. I'm an employee.

04:06.537 --> 04:08.869
Okay, well, do you really want
to get mollywhopped by my mama?

04:08.869 --> 04:10.751
All right, he's gonna
take us around

04:10.751 --> 04:14.174
because we are special V.I.P.s,
and he is the best.

04:14.174 --> 04:16.297
Oh, I assure you
you are in great hands.

04:16.297 --> 04:19.339
In fact, before I joined
the Disney family,

04:19.339 --> 04:21.642
I was a place kicker
for an arena football team.

04:21.642 --> 04:23.304
But that is a life
I left behind.

04:23.304 --> 04:24.725
-Hm.
-Okay.

04:24.725 --> 04:27.848
Okay! So, these are
your custom magic bands.

04:27.848 --> 04:28.519
-Thank you.
-Thank you.

04:28.519 --> 04:29.980
-Oh.
-All right.

04:29.980 --> 04:32.152
And because you are guests
at the Animal Kingdom Lodge,

04:32.152 --> 04:34.395
these will conveniently
charge your purchases.

04:34.395 --> 04:35.195
-Yay!
-Special.

04:35.195 --> 04:36.066
Babe, babe.

04:36.066 --> 04:36.737
-Hm.
-I like that.

04:36.737 --> 04:38.068
I wish you would!

04:38.068 --> 04:40.030
P-Pops. Pops,
what's wrong, man?

04:40.030 --> 04:41.742
Wait, you're mad that
we're doing it right?

04:41.742 --> 04:43.033
What the hell you
talking about, boy?

04:43.033 --> 04:44.575
We did it right when
I took you to Disneyland.

04:47.458 --> 04:49.209
Something wrong with
your tuna, baby?

04:49.209 --> 04:52.002
Pops, can I have
one of those?

04:52.002 --> 04:56.967
When you get a job,
yeah.

04:56.967 --> 04:59.630
-Well, I got a job now.
-And I have this.

04:59.630 --> 05:01.512
This is linked to
his credit card, yes?

05:01.512 --> 05:02.633
Yes.

05:02.633 --> 05:04.515
Come on, Ruby, let's go
make it rain at Epcot.

05:04.515 --> 05:06.096
-Oh, my.
-All right.

05:06.096 --> 05:07.808
Well, we're going
this way!

05:07.808 --> 05:09.520
-Let's go.
-All right.

05:09.520 --> 05:11.772
Excuse me.
V.I.P. coming through!

05:11.772 --> 05:14.355
V.I.P. coming through!

05:14.355 --> 05:16.026
So, we don't have to wait
in that line?

05:16.026 --> 05:18.108
Hah! Nope.
 But be gracious,

05:18.108 --> 05:19.780
because we're not better
than anybody else.

05:19.780 --> 05:21.862
Hell if we're not. I paid a lot
of money for us to be special.

05:21.862 --> 05:23.073
[ Cellphone rings ]

05:23.073 --> 05:24.114
You are special,
honey -- very.

05:24.114 --> 05:24.905
Hey, what's up?

05:24.905 --> 05:26.577
Nothin' much.

05:26.577 --> 05:29.039
Just, you know, handling some
B.I. on the Microsoft account.

05:29.039 --> 05:30.621
[ Chuckles ]
Quick question.

05:30.621 --> 05:32.543
Uh, asking for a friend,
all right?

05:32.543 --> 05:34.755
Uh, who is Microsoft?

05:34.755 --> 05:36.837
Hey, Charlie, I'm gonna
have to call you back, man.

05:36.837 --> 05:39.049
Right now you're distracting me
from feeling superior

05:39.049 --> 05:40.511
to the general-admission people
I'm passing.

05:40.511 --> 05:42.302
No, no, no, no, my friend's
back is against the wall,

05:42.302 --> 05:43.384
and you got to help him,
Dre.

05:43.384 --> 05:44.264
Come on, man -- p--

05:44.264 --> 05:45.426
Marshawn!
Marshawn Lynch!

05:45.426 --> 05:47.598
Oh, not him, man, not him.
But thank you.

05:47.598 --> 05:51.021
[ Chuckles ] That guy thought
you were Marshawn Lynch, Dad.

05:51.021 --> 05:54.685
Eh, it's just a flattering
form of racism, son.

05:54.685 --> 05:56.817
Now, anyone get
motion sickness?

05:56.817 --> 05:58.318
Anyone pregnant?

05:58.318 --> 06:01.652
Oh, oh, hey, hey.
Yes, I am actually pregnant.

06:01.652 --> 06:03.193
[ Gasps ] That's awesome,
congratulations.

06:03.193 --> 06:04.114
Thank you.

06:04.114 --> 06:05.406
But unfortunately,
mama bear,

06:05.406 --> 06:06.657
you're gonna have
to sit this ride out

06:06.657 --> 06:08.118
because of your cub
in the oven.

06:08.118 --> 06:11.992
Oh. Okay, well, there's a lot of
other rides I can ride, right?

06:11.992 --> 06:13.664
Oh, absolutely.

06:13.664 --> 06:15.255
Anything that doesn't have
a sharp tilt, turn, loop,

06:15.255 --> 06:17.047
sudden drop, or sudden stop.
[ Chuckles ]

06:17.047 --> 06:19.460
Wow, bae,
that's a lot you can't do.

06:19.460 --> 06:21.762
I know.

06:21.762 --> 06:23.464
Kind of I wish I didn't
pay extra for you now.

06:23.464 --> 06:24.174
Wha--

06:24.174 --> 06:25.175
Single rider!
 Dre.

06:25.175 --> 06:27.217
Bow wasn't going to ruin
 our trip

06:27.217 --> 06:29.430
the way the baby
 ruined hers.

06:29.430 --> 06:32.513
We were going to get down
 to the very important business

06:32.513 --> 06:34.475
of being
 very important people.

06:34.475 --> 06:36.437
My kids, they started off slow.

06:36.437 --> 06:37.608
Excuse us.

06:37.608 --> 06:39.399
I'm sorry.
I'm so sorry.

06:39.399 --> 06:41.692
Don't mind us.
We're with the guide.

06:41.692 --> 06:42.943
We're with Cody.

06:42.943 --> 06:44.485
What are you apologizing
for?

06:44.485 --> 06:46.026
You're V.I.P., boy.
Own this.

06:46.026 --> 06:48.529
But eventually, they started
 to get the hang of it.

06:48.529 --> 06:51.081
Don't hate!
V.I.P. coming through!

06:51.081 --> 06:52.663
It's natural
to feel jealous.

06:52.663 --> 06:54.034
Hey, we'll let you
know how it is.

06:54.034 --> 06:56.457
Don't make eye contact
with me.

06:56.457 --> 06:58.799
My God,
whose kids are those?

06:58.799 --> 07:01.041
They're mine!

07:01.041 --> 07:02.503
You all have fun!

07:02.503 --> 07:04.044
Cody. See you later!

07:04.044 --> 07:05.506
[ All chanting "V.I.P.!" ]

07:05.506 --> 07:08.719
♪ And I wouldn't
last these shows ♪

07:08.719 --> 07:13.644
♪ So I am headed home ♪

07:15.315 --> 07:17.938
Oh, so that's how it is.
Look here.

07:17.938 --> 07:19.480
[ Scoffs ]

07:19.480 --> 07:21.612
Waiter, we'd like
to buy a round

07:21.612 --> 07:23.524
for every sunburnt person
wearing a T-shirt

07:23.524 --> 07:24.865
courtesy
of our ungrateful son.

07:24.865 --> 07:26.657
[ Laughs ]
 [ All cheering ]

07:26.657 --> 07:28.989
Boy don't even realize
how much we had to sacrifice

07:28.989 --> 07:29.950
to pay for Disneyland.

07:29.950 --> 07:32.663
[ Dog barks in distance ]

07:44.044 --> 07:45.886
[ Siren wails in distance ]

07:45.886 --> 07:47.888
Earl!
That was my car!

07:47.888 --> 07:49.510
I bought them tickets.

07:49.510 --> 07:52.052
Opened up 17 Christmas cards
at the post office

07:52.052 --> 07:53.764
to get that money.
Boy never even thanked us.

07:53.764 --> 07:55.015
Ungrateful child.

07:55.015 --> 07:56.807
This is the worst ever.

07:56.807 --> 07:58.098
Well, now it is.

07:58.098 --> 07:59.520
[ Sighs ]

07:59.520 --> 08:02.022
Every ride I like
is off limits for me.

08:02.022 --> 08:03.814
I should've just
stayed home.

08:03.814 --> 08:07.738
I mean, I could've gotten
seven days alone in my house,

08:07.738 --> 08:10.611
no kids, no husband.

08:10.611 --> 08:12.242
No you.

08:12.242 --> 08:13.744
I can see how that
would be appealing.

08:13.744 --> 08:15.205
[ Flute plays ]

08:15.205 --> 08:18.118
You know...
I don't understand all the hype.

08:18.118 --> 08:19.459
Can't do anything here
that you can't do

08:19.459 --> 08:20.831
at the Chuck E. Cheese
in Torrance.

08:20.831 --> 08:21.962
Ooh, Black Jesus,

08:21.962 --> 08:24.585
if there was ever a time
to set myself on fire.

08:24.585 --> 08:28.178
Or...no fire, and we can
just go back to the hotel.

08:28.178 --> 08:29.429
I want to go back
to the hotel.

08:29.429 --> 08:32.131
That's the coward's way out.
But okay.

08:32.131 --> 08:35.054
Waiter!
One Tom Collins to go!

08:37.347 --> 08:40.100
You know, I don't see any other
V.I.P. guides out here.

08:40.100 --> 08:42.442
Are these people
not doing V.I.P.?

08:42.442 --> 08:43.693
They're not.

08:43.693 --> 08:46.026
I saw that kid in
the regular line -- twice.

08:46.026 --> 08:47.908
Oh, they're definitely not.

08:47.908 --> 08:50.150
That woman's wearing
Bugle Boy jeans.

08:50.150 --> 08:53.954
Hm. Cody.

08:53.954 --> 08:55.455
Let me holler at you
for a second, playboy.

08:55.455 --> 08:56.246
I like you.

08:56.246 --> 08:56.917
Oh.

08:56.917 --> 08:58.158
The kids like you.

08:58.158 --> 09:00.621
And I think you're
a great guy,

09:00.621 --> 09:02.502
but we traveled
clear across the country

09:02.502 --> 09:04.925
to have the most special week
of our lives.

09:04.925 --> 09:08.128
And if you think you're gonna
put us with non-V.I.P. people,

09:08.128 --> 09:09.469
ooh, I'm not the one,
Cody.

09:09.469 --> 09:10.340
Well --

09:10.340 --> 09:12.342
I'm not the one, Cody.

09:12.342 --> 09:13.634
Hm.

09:13.634 --> 09:16.176
Okay? Now, what is
the most popular ride here?

09:16.176 --> 09:19.059
And think good and hard
before you answer.

09:20.520 --> 09:21.852
Frozen Ever After
at Epcot.

09:21.852 --> 09:24.144
Oh, okay, take us
the most shaded route.

09:24.144 --> 09:24.945
[ Chuckles ]

09:24.945 --> 09:26.356
Johnsons!

09:26.356 --> 09:29.319
We out! Let's roll.
Lead the way, Cody.

09:29.319 --> 09:30.190
-Oh.
-Thank you.

09:32.192 --> 09:34.404
Well,
where's the damn exit?

09:34.404 --> 09:37.577
Hey, is this the line
to get out of here?

09:37.577 --> 09:39.620
No, it's the line
for Soarin' Around the World.

09:39.620 --> 09:41.001
Well, does it soar
back to my hotel?

09:41.001 --> 09:42.542
[ Chuckles ] No,
but it's air-conditioned.

09:42.542 --> 09:43.794
-Ooh.
-Ooh, air!

09:43.794 --> 09:44.875
-Let's go.
-All right. All right.

09:44.875 --> 09:46.707
-Come on in.
-Ooh.

09:46.707 --> 09:49.509
♪♪

09:54.675 --> 09:58.348
Yeah, I feel like I'm flying,
but I know I'm not.

09:58.348 --> 10:01.481
Soarin' Around the World?
Psht!

10:01.481 --> 10:03.724
[ Chuckles ] More like
Snorin' Around the World.

10:03.724 --> 10:05.185
[ Scoffs ]

10:05.185 --> 10:07.728
Whole wide,
amazing world.

10:07.728 --> 10:12.192
Ruby: It's terrible!
Just a lifelike illusion

10:12.192 --> 10:15.786
filled with majesty
and sensory delight.

10:15.786 --> 10:17.077
[ Chuckles ] Oh, yeah.

10:17.077 --> 10:18.659
[ People gasping ]

10:18.659 --> 10:20.120
Oh, we gonna hit the wall,
we gonna hit the wall!

10:20.120 --> 10:21.041
-What?!
-We gonna hit the wall!

10:24.835 --> 10:26.546
Well, I knew we
wasn't gonna hit it.

10:26.546 --> 10:28.418
Oh, Earl.

10:28.418 --> 10:30.841
Dre:
Here we go! Here we go!

10:30.841 --> 10:34.254
Seven Dwarfs Mine Train --
this is good, Jack.

10:34.254 --> 10:36.466
You can get a sneak peek
of jobs available

10:36.466 --> 10:37.637
to someone of your height.

10:37.637 --> 10:40.390
[ Screams ]

10:44.144 --> 10:46.646
My glasses!
I'm blind!

10:46.646 --> 10:49.940
Thank you, Disney gods!

10:49.940 --> 10:53.653
-Whoo!
-Yeah!

10:53.653 --> 10:56.036
Wow, guys,
what do you say?!

10:56.036 --> 10:57.487
-It was so much fun.
-Whoo!

10:57.487 --> 10:59.409
-Yeah!
-Why'd we stop?

10:59.409 --> 11:01.201
♪♪

11:01.201 --> 11:02.913
[ Elephant trumpets ]

11:04.915 --> 11:09.549
-Flamingos.
-Whoa, flamingos.

11:09.549 --> 11:10.881
Oh, my gosh.

11:10.881 --> 11:11.712
Is that a panda?

11:11.712 --> 11:12.843
This is awesome.

11:12.843 --> 11:14.845
You should see this,
Diane.

11:14.845 --> 11:16.426
I see it just fine.

11:16.426 --> 11:18.638
You're looking directly
into the sun.

11:18.638 --> 11:20.060
Oh, my stars.
Stop! Stop the truck!

11:20.060 --> 11:21.261
-Stop!
-What? What? What?

11:21.261 --> 11:22.853
Everybody, look over there.

11:22.853 --> 11:24.434
[ All gasping ]

11:24.434 --> 11:25.605
Oh, my God.
 What is it?

11:25.605 --> 11:26.476
[ Gasps ]

11:26.476 --> 11:28.188
Dear God,
somebody talk to me!

11:28.188 --> 11:30.731
Sweet Black Jesus,
this is beautiful.

11:30.731 --> 11:34.234
Ladies and gentlemen, I have
been on this ride 10,000 times.

11:34.234 --> 11:36.406
I -- I have a PhD
in animal behavior.

11:36.406 --> 11:39.409
I have spent two days in the
pouch of an Australian kangaroo,

11:39.409 --> 11:42.622
and I have [inhales]
never seen something like this.

11:42.622 --> 11:44.084
Describe it to me!

11:44.084 --> 11:47.207
There's only one word
for this --

11:47.207 --> 11:48.789
Indescribable.

11:48.789 --> 11:50.090
Yes.
 What?

11:50.090 --> 11:52.252
It's like seeing
the face of God.

11:52.252 --> 11:54.504
This is not only
the circle of life.

11:54.504 --> 11:55.926
This is the meaning
of life.

11:55.926 --> 11:57.007
-Yes.
-What?

11:57.007 --> 11:58.969
Well, take a picture.
Shoot a video!

11:58.969 --> 12:00.600
No, no.

12:00.600 --> 12:03.343
Let's use our mind cameras.

12:03.343 --> 12:04.224
Cody: Well said.

12:04.224 --> 12:06.346
What?
[ Exhales sharply ]

12:06.346 --> 12:08.148
See, that is why
we did V.I.P.

12:08.148 --> 12:11.311
Now, had we stood in the regular
line, we would have missed that.

12:11.311 --> 12:13.904
Uh, some of us did miss it.
It was Diane.

12:13.904 --> 12:15.445
Okay, hey. Hey, Cody.

12:15.445 --> 12:16.817
So, what's next?

12:16.817 --> 12:19.489
For you? I'm not sure.
Your time with me is up.

12:19.489 --> 12:20.821
Uh...

12:20.821 --> 12:22.662
Uh, but I bought you.

12:22.662 --> 12:25.365
Oh, that word again.

12:25.365 --> 12:26.997
You didn't actually buy me.

12:26.997 --> 12:28.708
You bought my services
for seven hours,

12:28.708 --> 12:29.870
and I've had a great time.

12:29.870 --> 12:31.792
I like you,
and I like your kids,

12:31.792 --> 12:33.924
but now it's time for me
to go back to H.Q.

12:33.924 --> 12:36.797
and change out of my socks
and be with the Gonzalez family.

12:36.797 --> 12:38.799
Okay.
 But please know
you've got a friend in me.

12:38.799 --> 12:39.759
Okay, Cody, so --

12:39.759 --> 12:40.680
You've got a friend in me.

12:40.680 --> 12:41.842
But, Cody --
 Dre.

12:41.842 --> 12:43.844
You got a friend in me.

12:43.844 --> 12:45.645
Hm? Bye.
[ Chuckles ]

12:45.645 --> 12:46.476
Bye.

12:46.476 --> 12:47.727
-Bye.
-Bye?

12:47.727 --> 12:49.059
-Wait, what?
-Is this a joke?

12:49.059 --> 12:51.481
Cody? I told you
I am not the one!

12:53.193 --> 12:54.734
[ Voice breaking ]
I am not the one!

12:54.734 --> 12:56.656
We're in gen-pop?

12:56.656 --> 13:01.031
Nooooooooooo!

13:01.031 --> 13:01.701
[ Crying ]

13:05.785 --> 13:06.997
Okay, look, guys.

13:06.997 --> 13:09.789
I know losing V.I.P.
is not great, but, hey, look.

13:09.789 --> 13:12.582
We're still at Disney World.

13:12.582 --> 13:15.125
And this line
is only 25 minutes.

13:15.125 --> 13:16.506
-[ Sighs ]
-25 minutes?

13:16.506 --> 13:17.257
Mm-hmm.

13:20.180 --> 13:22.973
[ Gasping ] No.
Fix this!

13:22.973 --> 13:25.015
Fix this now!

13:25.015 --> 13:26.806
I can't see how far
we've fallen,

13:26.806 --> 13:28.188
but I can feel it.
 [ Stomping ]

13:28.188 --> 13:32.192
♪ So I -- I am headed home ♪

13:34.194 --> 13:36.486
Okay, let's do this.

13:36.486 --> 13:38.358
Uh...

13:38.358 --> 13:41.611
M-Microsoft.
'Cause that's who you are.

13:41.611 --> 13:43.363
[ Chuckles ]

13:43.363 --> 13:45.325
Uh...

13:45.325 --> 13:50.330
Uh, here at Stevens & Lido,
there's a little exercise we do.

13:50.330 --> 13:55.415
Uh, let's pretend as if I have
absolutely no idea who you are,

13:55.415 --> 13:57.918
what you do,
or anything about your company.

13:57.918 --> 14:00.881
Tell me what you want
me to do, all right?

14:00.881 --> 14:02.883
Step by step.
[ Chuckles ]

14:02.883 --> 14:05.015
Talk to me like a man
who's laid everything

14:05.015 --> 14:09.099
on the line for a job
he's completely unqualified for.

14:09.099 --> 14:12.062
[ Sighs ] That was
a manipulative ride back there.

14:12.062 --> 14:14.144
Yeah, playing with
our emotions.

14:14.144 --> 14:16.026
Heh, making us feel
more alive

14:16.026 --> 14:17.357
than we've ever felt
and whatnot.

14:17.357 --> 14:18.858
Can't wait to
get out of here.

14:18.858 --> 14:20.860
Hey, should we get in
that exit line over there?

14:20.860 --> 14:23.363
No, that exit line looks way
too rough for a pregnant lady.

14:23.363 --> 14:24.945
Oh, I think we should
get in that exit line.

14:24.945 --> 14:26.536
Looks a lot gentler.

14:26.536 --> 14:30.450
Or maybe get in that stupid
Dumbo exit line over there.

14:30.450 --> 14:34.254
Maybe sneak out above the clouds
on that adorable elephant.

14:34.254 --> 14:35.415
Yeah, yeah, if you think
that's the fastest way

14:35.415 --> 14:36.957
for us to get of here,
come on, let's go.

14:36.957 --> 14:37.958
That's the fastest way.

14:37.958 --> 14:41.881
I'm right behind you.

14:41.881 --> 14:43.503
Most people die
climbing Everest.

14:43.503 --> 14:45.215
We're gonna die
waiting to ride it.

14:45.215 --> 14:47.007
I hate my life right now.

14:47.007 --> 14:48.718
I hate my dad right now.

14:48.718 --> 14:50.810
Uh...

14:50.810 --> 14:52.392
Are you kidding me?

14:52.392 --> 14:54.514
Huh?

14:54.514 --> 14:57.017
You wait in one line,
and you have a meltdown?

14:57.017 --> 14:59.609
You had an incredible day!

14:59.609 --> 15:02.822
You got to ride
like 20 rides in 10 minutes!

15:02.822 --> 15:05.075
You got to go ahead
of Green Day.

15:05.075 --> 15:07.697
Did you see puss
on Tré Cool?

15:07.697 --> 15:10.740
Huh?
And you know what's worse?

15:10.740 --> 15:13.083
Not one person
has even said thank you.

15:13.083 --> 15:14.374
Gee, thanks, Dad.

15:14.374 --> 15:15.535
Shut up!

15:15.535 --> 15:19.709
Not sincere.
You monsters are dead to me!

15:19.709 --> 15:22.963
[ People gasp ]

15:22.963 --> 15:24.965
Okay, maybe that was
the wrong choice of words,

15:24.965 --> 15:26.636
since I am your father,

15:26.636 --> 15:28.008
but I hate you.

15:28.008 --> 15:28.718
[ Gasps ]

15:28.718 --> 15:29.719
Excuse me.

15:29.719 --> 15:30.850
Excuse me, sorry.

15:30.850 --> 15:32.182
I'm sorry.
Let me through here.

15:32.182 --> 15:34.814
I'm sorry. Oh, yes!
I'm still mad at you!

15:34.814 --> 15:36.266
[ People gasp ]
 Excuse me. Excuse me.

15:42.942 --> 15:43.773
Sir.

15:43.773 --> 15:44.864
Hm? Yes.

15:44.864 --> 15:46.326
Sir, we're lost.

15:46.326 --> 15:47.567
We keep looking
for the exits,

15:47.567 --> 15:51.071
and instead,
we keep finding gift shops.

15:51.071 --> 15:53.283
Only reason I'm wearing
this hat is 'cause my grandkids

15:53.283 --> 15:55.875
made me get it and you know,
the ears protect my neck.

15:55.875 --> 15:57.747
[ Chuckles ]

15:57.747 --> 16:00.500
And this tiara, I hate how it
takes 25 years off my real age.

16:00.500 --> 16:01.211
-Oh.
-Mm-hmm.

16:01.211 --> 16:02.132
[ Chuckling ]
I hate that.

16:02.132 --> 16:03.543
Well, some of the exits

16:03.543 --> 16:05.295
are gonna be right over here.
 Oh, look, guys.

16:05.295 --> 16:06.966
There's a real exit
right -- right there.

16:06.966 --> 16:07.927
[ Marching band plays ]

16:07.927 --> 16:08.928
Yep, that's one of them.

16:08.928 --> 16:10.470
Oh, no.
Parade's coming through.

16:10.470 --> 16:12.012
Announcer: And now we
invite you to relax --

16:12.012 --> 16:13.553
Well, you folks can cross.
There's still time.

16:13.553 --> 16:15.685
No, no, no, no, no.
No, no, no, she's pregnant.

16:15.685 --> 16:16.516
Yeah.

16:16.516 --> 16:17.517
And we're elderly.

16:17.517 --> 16:19.019
Mm.

16:19.019 --> 16:20.940
So, uh, you know,
we'll just sit here and suffer

16:20.940 --> 16:25.485
while this...
magnificent parade goes by.

16:25.485 --> 16:27.777
I don't know how this day
could get any worse.

16:27.777 --> 16:29.529
I don't either.
It's horrible!

16:29.529 --> 16:31.031
So hot.

16:31.031 --> 16:32.492
♪ Be our guest, be our guest ♪

16:32.492 --> 16:34.374
♪ Put our service to the test ♪

16:34.374 --> 16:36.116
♪ Tie your napkin
'round your neck, chérie,

16:36.116 --> 16:37.417
and we'll provide the rest ♪

16:37.417 --> 16:39.289
♪ Soup du jour,
hot hors d'oeuvres ♪

16:39.289 --> 16:40.830
♪ Why, we only live to serve ♪

16:40.830 --> 16:42.502
♪ Try the gray stuff,
it's delicious ♪

16:42.502 --> 16:44.124
♪ Don't believe me,
ask the dishes ♪

16:44.124 --> 16:45.925
♪ Go on, unfold your menu ♪

16:45.925 --> 16:47.627
♪ Take a glance
and then you'll ♪

16:47.627 --> 16:49.389
♪ Be our guest, be our guest,
be our guest ♪

16:49.389 --> 16:51.341
[ Laughter ]

16:51.341 --> 16:53.553
[ People cheering ]

16:53.553 --> 16:56.476
[ Scoffs ]
Oh, look, Junior.

16:56.476 --> 17:00.730
There's another
super cool guy.

17:00.730 --> 17:03.773
Oh, my God!

17:03.773 --> 17:06.276
A Jedi girl!

17:06.276 --> 17:08.858
She's my Rey.

17:08.858 --> 17:10.910
You should talk to her.

17:10.910 --> 17:13.242
This could actually
be something.

17:13.242 --> 17:15.204
I mean, it won't,
but it could be.

17:15.204 --> 17:17.247
It won't,
just so you know.

17:17.247 --> 17:19.368
Okay, I've got some
great ice breakers.

17:19.368 --> 17:20.750
Check this out.
[ Clears throat ]

17:20.750 --> 17:23.333
Do you have a quarter?

17:23.333 --> 17:26.626
I told my mom I'd call her
as soon as I fell in love.

17:26.626 --> 17:29.929
I would use the quarter on
a thing called a pay phone.

17:29.929 --> 17:32.722
I've never had a girlfriend,
but that seems very wrong.

17:32.722 --> 17:33.803
Fine.
You know what?

17:33.803 --> 17:35.845
I'll just go with "Hi."

17:35.845 --> 17:37.767
How hard's "Hi"?

17:37.767 --> 17:40.520
Hi.
[ Higher-pitched ] Hi.

17:40.520 --> 17:42.852
Hi!

17:42.852 --> 17:45.525
[ High-pitched ]
Hellooooo!

17:50.450 --> 17:52.902
♪♪

17:52.902 --> 17:56.406
Hey.

17:56.406 --> 17:57.997
Are you allowed
to eat that?

17:57.997 --> 17:59.829
Hope so.
It's my second one.

17:59.829 --> 18:01.831
Why are you wearing
Mickey hands?

18:01.831 --> 18:04.124
Oh, no big deal.

18:04.124 --> 18:07.167
I was in a parade
with your parents,

18:07.167 --> 18:10.170
who I had the best day
ever with!

18:10.170 --> 18:12.762
Oh.
Never tell Ruby.

18:12.762 --> 18:15.975
Well, I had the worst day ever
with your spoiled-ass kids.

18:15.975 --> 18:17.096
[ Trash can lid thuds ]

18:17.096 --> 18:18.268
You should've seen them,
Bow.

18:18.268 --> 18:20.850
The second we lost
V.I.P. status,

18:20.850 --> 18:23.223
they turned into
ungrateful monsters.

18:23.223 --> 18:26.065
Huh.
Well, you know what?

18:26.065 --> 18:28.728
hey were probably just
following your lead.

18:28.728 --> 18:31.821
Bow, I was just trying to make
Disney World extra special.

18:31.821 --> 18:33.493
Dre,

18:33.493 --> 18:36.996
you stepped over a baby
in stroller to get on a ride.

18:36.996 --> 18:38.618
Okay. Okay, Bow.
All right.

18:38.618 --> 18:41.951
I probably did mess it up
for everybody.

18:41.951 --> 18:45.165
Maybe not for everybody.
Look over there, babe.

18:45.165 --> 18:46.706
Look.

18:46.706 --> 18:47.707
[ Laughter ]

18:47.707 --> 18:50.089
Laughing.
Probably at me.

18:50.089 --> 18:51.591
[ Chuckles ]

18:51.591 --> 18:54.594
Dre, not everything
is about you.

18:54.594 --> 18:56.846
[ Scoffs ]
Yes, it is.

18:56.846 --> 18:58.808
Okay, you know what?

18:58.808 --> 19:01.521
Actually,
in some weird way,

19:01.521 --> 19:03.603
it's probably a good thing
that you threw a tantrum

19:03.603 --> 19:06.266
and abandoned them,
'cause look.

19:06.266 --> 19:09.319
It gave them the space to
actually enjoy each other.

19:09.319 --> 19:11.731
Hm.

19:11.731 --> 19:15.985
Yeah, you're right.

19:15.985 --> 19:18.328
I really did save the day.

19:18.328 --> 19:21.120
[ Sighs ] Yeah, Dre,
you're a hero.

19:21.120 --> 19:22.332
Yes, I am.

19:22.332 --> 19:24.163
Junior got a girl's number.

19:24.163 --> 19:24.914
I did.

19:24.914 --> 19:26.286
But he lost it on the ride.

19:26.286 --> 19:27.337
I did.

19:27.337 --> 19:28.878
All right, come on,
tell me about it.

19:28.878 --> 19:30.790
Sweetheart,
where are your glasses?

19:30.790 --> 19:32.051
As it turned out,

19:32.051 --> 19:34.003
we didn't need
 to have V.I.P. status

19:34.003 --> 19:35.425
to have a special experience.

19:35.425 --> 19:36.636
-Nice!
-Eat that!

19:36.636 --> 19:40.640
[ People gasping, murmuring ]

19:40.640 --> 19:42.932
Oh, my gosh.

19:42.932 --> 19:47.307
♪ When you wish upon a star ♪

19:47.307 --> 19:48.478
[ All cheering ]

19:48.478 --> 19:52.151
♪ Makes no difference
who you are ♪

19:52.151 --> 19:56.866
♪ Anything your heart desires ♪
 Awesome!

19:56.866 --> 19:59.869
♪ Will come to you ♪
 Wow!

19:59.869 --> 20:01.531
Beautiful, huh?

20:01.531 --> 20:02.822
Yeah, son, it is.

20:02.822 --> 20:05.375
♪ If your heart
is in your dream ♪

20:05.375 --> 20:07.417
You know what would
go good with this?

20:07.417 --> 20:08.328
No. What?

20:08.328 --> 20:09.669
♪ No request is too extreme ♪

20:09.669 --> 20:12.422
Tuna sandwich.

20:12.422 --> 20:14.213
[ Both laugh ]
 ♪ When you wish upon a star ♪

20:14.213 --> 20:18.047
Yeah, you might be
right about that.

20:18.047 --> 20:19.469
♪ As dreamers do ♪

20:19.469 --> 20:22.432
I wish you would.

20:22.432 --> 20:25.765
♪♪

20:33.653 --> 20:35.695
[ Both laugh ]

20:44.243 --> 20:45.124
All right, guys.

20:45.124 --> 20:47.246
I just got to say that was
the best trip I've ever been on.

20:47.246 --> 20:48.328
You know, my favorite part --

20:50.039 --> 20:52.632
[ Doors closing ]

20:52.632 --> 20:57.547
[ Sighs ] I truly am alone
in this life.

20:57.547 --> 20:59.218
Why the long face?

20:59.218 --> 21:00.760
Charlie, why are you
in my house?

21:00.760 --> 21:02.512
I've always wanted
to stay here.

21:02.512 --> 21:05.184
Once it came up on Airbnb,
I knew I had to get it.

21:05.184 --> 21:07.016
It's the only house on the block
that eluded me.

21:07.016 --> 21:08.518
What?

21:08.518 --> 21:11.441
Left your main man flapping
in the breeze, huh?

21:11.441 --> 21:14.193
Should've just told me Microsoft
was a computer company.

21:14.193 --> 21:15.445
Uh...

21:15.445 --> 21:18.698
So, you were in my house
alone all week?

21:18.698 --> 21:21.321
Yeah. [ Gasps ]

21:21.321 --> 21:23.863
Eustace!

21:23.863 --> 21:25.575
-Mom...
-Shh, Daddy's working.
